name: Lexington City Hall
notes:
Returning Your Ballot

Absentee ballots returned by mail must be postmarked on or before Election Day (Tuesday, November 3) and received in our office by Tuesday, November 10.
Voters may also drop off their own voted absentee ballot in person at the Anoka County Government Center or at their city hall*. Ballots must be dropped off by 3 p.m. on Election Day in order to be counted. 

If you are returning someone else's ballot, you will need to sign a return log and show identification with name and signature.

You may not drop your ballot off at your polling place on election day.
Within the last 7 days prior to the election, voters in special situations can use the agent delivery process to vote absentee.

name: Edina City Hall
notes:
Drivers will enter lot from 50th Street and follow signs to the drop-off tent, which will be staffed. After turning in their  ballot, drivers will follow signs to exit onto Grange Road. 

Important Steps for Dropping Off Completed Absentee Ballot
Ballots may not be dropped off inside City Hall. Wait in the drive-thru line.
Only ballots from Edina voters accepted.
Voters should bring only the Signature Envelope with their ballot sealed inside. Do not bring the mailing/transmittal envelope.
Make sure to put both your driver’s license number and the last four digits of your social security number on your Signature Envelope. This ensures it will match what you submitted when registering and prevent your ballot from being rejected.
Sign your Signature Envelope before you arrive. If you are registering to vote as well, make sure a witness has also signed the envelope.
When you arrive at the drop-off tent, staff will inspect each Signature Envelope to make sure it has all the above information. Missing information slows the process.
A voter dropping off someone else’s ballot must show Elections staff their own identification and fill out an agent delivery log.
Please be patient and expect a wait if dropping off your ballot. Following the above steps will speed the process for everyone. To avoid lines, mail your ballot instead.

Note: Ballots must be dropped off by 3 p.m. Nov. 3
